title: AWS service status RSS feed
agents: aws_status_rss
catalog: cloud/aws
license: GPLv3
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the per-service status RSS/Atom feeds published by
 AWS at https://status.aws.amazon.com/. For every feed configured in the
 special agent rule the check verifies that the feed is reachable and
 contains valid XML data, and inspects the most recent published entry.

 The service goes {CRIT} when the feed cannot be fetched or parsed (HTTP
 error, timeout, non-XML response). If the feed is healthy and contains
 no entries at all, AWS is currently not reporting any incident for that
 service and the state is {OK}. When the newest entry is younger than
 the configured thresholds, the service goes {WARN} or {CRIT}.

item:
 The configured service name, e.g. {Amazon CloudFront}.

discovery:
 One service is discovered for every feed entry returned by the
 special agent.
